0033>10:10:07 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: It's not that hard - part I (Assisting)</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I would just like to add something.  I know I'm a druid, but my husband's a warrior and he usually is the main assist:<br>
<br>
DO NOT HIT ASSIST UNTIL THE PRIMARY ASSIST CALLS IT, DANGIT!!!!<br>
<br>
I have seen way the heck too many mobs rip a chanter a new one because people hit assist too soon.  Unless you have turned your assist off, the first thing you're going to do is hit the mob.<br>
<br>
The primary saying &quot;Hail a_mob_00&quot; is NOT calling assist.  He is taunting.  He will, in general, taunt TWICE.  This will, theoretically, make the mob hate the primary more than it hates the chanter that's been keeping it immobile for the past 5 minutes.  If you just keep laying on the assist button, you will break that mez before the primary has a chance to get its attention.  When the primary says &quot;Assist me on { a_mob_00 }&quot; or whatever cute little message he chooses, THEN and ONLY THEN do you hit your &quot;assist&quot; button.<br>
<br>
The other reason is that the primary is, pretty darn often, also the peeler.  When you peel, you have several things on you.  If any of these hit you, and you just happen to riposte, you will target the mob you riposted, whether that's the mob you wanted or not.  I've seen way too many people get the wrong target due to a riposte.  Pay attention.  If the primary is yelling &quot;Assist me on a black reaver&quot; and your little bar over on the right says &quot;a phantom&quot;, then there's a really good chance that somehow you got on the wrong mob.  <br>
<br>
Third thing:  PAY ATTENTION TO SWITCH CALLS.  Don't walk up, hit assist, and go get a soda.  Some mobs cannot be mezzed.  Some mobs types randomly have mobs that can't be mezzed and the chanter won't know until he or she tries.  At that point, the primary will usually change targets so that the current target can be mezzed.  If you keep hitting the current target, the current target won't be mezzed, and you'll have a naked and very ticked off chanter on your tail.<br>
<br>
Fourth:  Spells that don't do damage don't break mez.  Cool huh.  So people, stop yelling when someone is tashing, slowing, or snaring mobs that are mezzed, because those spells won't break it.  I usually walk around snaring every mezzed mob during the fights, because snare is high aggro and will transfer the aggro to me if the mob comes unmezzed, giving the chanter a few seconds to re-mez while the mob smacks me silly.<br>
<br>
-fel</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukaedian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaedian</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.silentavengers.net/pictures/kaedian/smallskull.jpg BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>h0x0r!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>5/11/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>10:36:14 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: It's not that hard - part I (Assisting)</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Siphon Strength<br>
