<br>
Please do not try to taunt anything off of me when I'm trying to mez it other than by hitting the taunt button or using some sort of non-mez breaking spell.  If the mob kills me, it's going to be either <br>
<br>
1)  My fault for not being able to mez it<br>
or<br>
2)  Your (General sense, no one specific here) fault for breaking my mez by trying to "help" me.<br>
<br>
I come equipped with a full line of spells to help me do my job, and part of my job includes getting beaten on while trying to mez something.  I can channel through very well.<br>
<br>
I understand a lot of people would love to help, but I'd rather be pissed at myself for not being able to control the situation than be pissed at someone for getting me killed by trying to help.  <br>
<br>
Furthermore, enchanters on raids help each other out, and unless it's a really big pull - if I'm getting beaten on and not getting the mez off, it's a pretty sure bet some other enchanter has noticed this and is working on helping me mez the mob.<br>
<br>
In a non-raid situation, well, there things are different, of course, and as long as you let me know what you're planning on doing beforehand, I won't have a problem with it.<br>
<br>
But as far as raids go, I appreciate the help, really, I do, but unless the puller switches to that particular mob, please don't attempt hitting it or trying to get the taunt off to you in any way that could POSSIBLY break the mez.<br>
<br>
To summarize:<br>
I'm sure every enchanter has his/her own play style, but my opinion is that I'd rather go one-on-one with the mob I'm trying to mez or be backed up by another enchanter or DIE trying to CC it than die because someone accidentally (even with good intentions, which I'm sure are behind almost all "accidental" breaks) broke my mezzed a_very_painful_mob00.</font><P><center><img src = http://members.bellatlantic.net/~mezner/daeonsig2.jpg><br>
