Nice post.  Two wee comments:<br>
<br>
1.  The above also applies ta groups without an enchanter, where someone else (fer instance a cleric <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) is handling crowd-control duties.<br>
<br>
2.  I doubt this is news, but I discovered this neat trick by accident:  if ye want ta assist without breaking mez, especially in close quarters, assist while sitting.  This'll set the target, and ye'll also get an &quot;Auto attack off.&quot; message, so ye can stand and prepare ta melee or cast without aggroing the mob.<br>
<br>
</font><P>Cheers,<br>
